+/* input-menu-pin r35 (transformations/path-explosion/input-menu-pin):
+ *
+ * r35 grows r34's menu from 345 to 346 documents, each <= the 40-byte symbolic
+ * file. r34's directed ceiling battery flagged one reachable seam in
+ * xmlParseStartTag2's namespace-validation; r35 absorbs it. 1 rep, confirmed by
+ * reproducible per-candidate stable line-set (3 FRESH full-menu baselines, merge
+ * artifacts xmlIO.c:2718-2723 + dict.c:637 pre-filtered), +5 distinct lines:
+ *   - <a xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/xmlns/"  binding the DEFAULT namespace to
+ *       the reserved `xmlns` namespace URI -> parser.c:8881-8885, the
+ *       XML_NS_ERR_XML_NAMESPACE "reuse of the xmlns namespace name is forbidden"
+ *       branch. (40-byte truncated form; the trailing "/>" is the legal-XML
+ *       trailing-space concretisation the pin adds.)
+ * A directed battery over the `xmlns:prefix=`-value validation branches
+ * (xmlns:xmlns redefinition 8920, xmlns:p="" empty 8934, xmlns:xml wrong-URI 8901,
+ * invalid-URI warning 8944) added 0 -- those are already covered by r24's
+ * namespace docs; the xml-namespace-URI (36-char) variants need a doc >40 bytes
+ * (file-width-bound).
+ *
+ * Yields keep shrinking (+6 r33, +1 r34, +5 r35) but each DIRECTED round still
+ * finds a reproducible reachable seam (broad probing saturated at r32). The
+ * campaign approaches but has not reached the ceiling.
+ *
+ * Methodology (r17/r19/r23-r34): a lead is judged by its REPRODUCIBLE
+ * per-candidate stable LINE-SET over >=3 FRESH FULL-MENU baselines with the known
+ * merge artifacts pre-filtered, set-covered. The ceiling check pairs a BROAD
+ * battery with a DIRECTED battery at the function-mapped reachable residual.
+ *
+ * Mechanism identical to r1-r34: one symbolic klee_range selects one menu entry;
+ * KLEE forks once and explores all 346 in a SINGLE run; each is fully
+ * concretised (entry bytes + trailing spaces, legal XML Misc* after the root)
+ * so the ktest replays identically on the baseline coverage binary and the
+ * downstream parse/build/serialise is fork-free.
+ *
+ * klee_range / klee_assume are declared weak (not via <klee/klee.h>) so the
+ * native coverage binary -- which links libxml2.a after -lklee-stubs and would
+ * otherwise drop the stub archive before these references appear -- links with
+ * the symbols resolving to null; get-bc then extracts the bitcode where KLEE
+ * supplies the real intrinsics. This is the idiom the other library-based
+ * harnesses (jasper, libtiff) use.
+ */
+extern int  klee_range(int begin, int end, const char *name) __attribute__((weak));
+extern void klee_assume(unsigned long condition) __attribute__((weak));
